@host = https://localhost:7113
# Paste a Bearer token from your Keycloak portal client (see GETTING_STARTED.md). Endpoints require auth
# when Keycloak is configured; the Identity endpoints additionally require the "Identity.Admin" role.
@token = REPLACE_WITH_JWT

### Liveness probe (no auth) — process is responsive
GET {{host}}/alive

### Readiness probe (no auth) — DB connectivity + migrations healthy
GET {{host}}/health

### List users (paged) — requires Identity.Admin
GET {{host}}/api/identity/users?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get a single user by external (Keycloak) id — requires Identity.Admin
GET {{host}}/api/identity/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Queue a notification (any authenticated user)
POST {{host}}/api/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recipientUserId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "recipientEmail": "user@example.com",
  "channel": "Email",
  "subject": "Hello from the API",
  "body": "This is a test notification."
}

### Queue a notification idempotently — retrying with the SAME Idempotency-Key replays the first response
# (no duplicate). Send this twice and compare: the second carries header "Idempotency-Replayed: true".
POST {{host}}/api/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: 3f1a6b2c-0001-demo-key-aaaaaaaaaaaa

{
  "recipientUserId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "recipientEmail": "user@example.com",
  "channel": "Email",
  "subject": "Idempotent send",
  "body": "Safe to retry."
}

###
